    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels for MRL 2. Software quality assurance (L2), numerical code verification (L2), discretization error (L2, GCI=4.1%), test conditions (L2), output comparison (L2, mean error 8.7%), relevance of QoIs (L2), and relevance of validation activities to the COU (L2) are all satisfied. Six factors are appropriately scoped out under MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40-2018 Table 1, with documented rationale for each. The provenance chain from raw experimental data through post-processing activities to validation results is complete. Uncertainty quantification is documented for both validation results. The model is judged credible for its intended use: identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under CPB conditions at MRL 2. No shortfalls exist; no offset rationale is required.",
